KPIS (Key Performance Indicator)

ðŸ“Š 1. Strategic KPIs
	Measure long-term business goals.
	Example: Revenue Growth Rate, Market Share, Customer Satisfaction Score (CSAT).
ðŸ“‰ 2. Operational KPIs
	Track daily or weekly business processes.
	Example: Production Efficiency, Inventory Turnover, Customer Response Time.
ðŸ“Œ 3. Leading vs. Lagging KPIs
	Leading KPIs â€“ Predict future performance (e.g Sales Pipeline Value).
	Lagging KPIs â€“ Measure past performance (e.g  Annual Revenue).

